quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  41,1,"Ha Mīm."
  41,2,"A bestowal from on high by the All-Merciful, the Bestower of mercy—"
  41,3,"a Scripture whose signs1were detailed as an Arabic Recital2for people who know."
  41,4,"A herald of glad tidings and a warner, but most of them disregard(it), so they do not hear."
  41,5,"And they said, “Our hearts are screened from what yousg call us to, and in our ears is deafness, and between us and you is a barrier. So do what you want, and so will we.”"
  41,6,"Saysg , “I am only a human being like youpl . To me it is revealed that your god is One God. So be upright towards Him and seek forgiveness from Him.” And woe to the polytheists—"
  41,7,"those who do not bring about the purifying act1, and regarding the Hereafter they are deniers."
  41,8,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds—for them is an unfailing reward."
  41,9,"Say, “Can it be that youpl really deny the One Who created the earth in two(heavenly) days and attribute rivals to Him? That is the Lord of all realms.”"
  41,10,"And He made therein firm mountains on top of it, and He blessed it and determined its sustenance in four days, equal,1 for those who ask."